This paper discusses the use of digital platforms such as Facebook for conducting online surveys and studying human behavior, which falls under the category of computational social science (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the use of data synchronization with the national census and Afrobarometer survey, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) and statistical learning (cs.SD). The paper also discusses the comparison of audience estimates with population estimates, which falls under the category of computer science and society (cs.CS). Finally, the paper discusses the characteristics of online respondents, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
